content.description:
Finger crack in a short but striking left facing corner with a death flake above. Flake was pulled on during the our ground up ascent and seemed solid. From the top of the corner rest up, because you have a brutal 10 feet of wide crack to go. Gear anchor on top

Named in honor of Ahria “Adu” Ross and

Rosebud Garcia Bret Harte

Two Shuteye Legends.
content.protection: Small stuff for the finger crack, and if you have something 8” wide for the top bring it! Jeremy didn’t.
content.location: Far left side of the crag. Sweeping corner, can’t miss it.

climbs.name: Jamcracker
climbs.fa: Grahm Doe, Justin and Jeremy Ross

content.description: Splitter cracks like this are few and far between along shuteye ridge. This truly is a 4 star route with excellent gear and a puzzling crux.
content.location: If you’ve found Ahria wall then you’ve found this crack.
